---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="WebRoutines — Privacy"
  description="WebRoutines privacy policy. All data is stored locally in your browser. No accounts, no analytics, no tracking."
  ogTitle="WebRoutines Privacy"
  ogDescription="Local-first by design. No data leaves your browser."
  activePage="privacy"
>
  <main class="relative z-10 flex-1 pb-8 pt-8">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-[1400px] px-6">

      <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent/10">
          <svg class="h-4 w-4 text-accent" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h1 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-fg">WebRoutines Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-sm text-fg-faint">Last updated February 2026</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-accent/20 bg-accent/5 p-5">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-accent">The short version</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">
          WebRoutines stores all data locally in your browser. Nothing is sent to any server. There are no accounts, no analytics, and no tracking. Your browsing routines stay on your machine.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- What we store -->
      <section class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-fg">What data is stored</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface p-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-medium text-fg">Routine definitions</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">Names and ordered URL lists you create. Stored in IndexedDB, a browser-managed local database.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface p-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-medium text-fg">Run history</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">Start time, duration, steps completed, and completion status for each routine run. Stored in IndexedDB.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface p-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-medium text-fg">Settings</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">Theme preference, tab loading mode, and feature toggles. Stored in Chrome's local extension storage.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface p-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-medium text-fg">Session state</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">Active runner state (which routine is running, current step, tab IDs). Stored in session-scoped storage that clears when the browser closes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- What we don't do -->
      <section class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-fg">What WebRoutines does not do</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-fg-muted">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-5 w-5 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-surface text-fg-faint">&times;</span>
            <span>Does not transmit any data to external servers.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-5 w-5 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-surface text-fg-faint">&times;</span>
            <span>Does not include analytics, telemetry, or tracking of any kind.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-5 w-5 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-surface text-fg-faint">&times;</span>
            <span>Does not require or offer user accounts.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-5 w-5 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-surface text-fg-faint">&times;</span>
            <span>Does not read, collect, or store page content from sites you visit.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-5 w-5 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-surface text-fg-faint">&times;</span>
            <span>Does not inject ads or promotional content.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Permissions -->
      <section class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Permissions and why</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">WebRoutines requests only the permissions necessary for its features.</p>
        <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-surface-border">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-surface-border bg-surface">
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-fg-faint">Permission</th>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-fg-faint">Reason</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-fg-muted">
              <tr class="border-b border-surface-border">
                <td class="px-4 py-3"><code class="font-mono text-xs text-fg">storage</code></td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Persist routines, run history, and settings locally.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-surface-border">
                <td class="px-4 py-3"><code class="font-mono text-xs text-fg">sidePanel</code></td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Display the main extension interface in Chrome's side panel.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-surface-border">
                <td class="px-4 py-3"><code class="font-mono text-xs text-fg">tabGroups</code></td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Create and manage tab groups for routine runners.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-surface-border">
                <td class="px-4 py-3"><code class="font-mono text-xs text-fg">unlimitedStorage</code></td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Support larger local datasets as run history grows.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3"><code class="font-mono text-xs text-fg">host permissions</code></td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Required for the focus mode controller to appear on web pages. The controller does not read or modify page content — it only renders a navigation overlay.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Data lifecycle -->
      <section class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Data lifecycle</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-fg-muted">
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface p-4">
            <p class="font-medium text-fg">You create it</p>
            <p class="mt-1 leading-relaxed">Routines are created through the extension UI and stored in your browser's IndexedDB.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface p-4">
            <p class="font-medium text-fg">You control it</p>
            <p class="mt-1 leading-relaxed">Edit, delete, or export routines at any time. Import/export is user-initiated only. There is no background sync.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface p-4">
            <p class="font-medium text-fg">You remove it</p>
            <p class="mt-1 leading-relaxed">Uninstalling the extension removes all extension-managed data per Chrome's default behavior. Export your routines first if you want to keep them.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Static site -->
      <section class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-fg">This website</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">
          This is a static site hosted on GitHub Pages. It does not use cookies, analytics scripts, or any form of user tracking. There are no third-party scripts loaded beyond Google Fonts.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <section class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">
          Questions about this policy can be directed to the repository's issue tracker or via email at <span class="text-fg">[your-email@example.com]</span>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Policy updates -->
      <section class="mt-10 rounded-lg border border-surface-border bg-surface/60 p-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">
          <span class="font-medium text-fg">Policy updates:</span> This privacy page is versioned alongside the source code. Changes to data handling behavior will be reflected here in the same commit. Check the repository history for the full changelog.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
